readme:
# DEPRECATED

# It is now (snippets@0.45.0, 2014-06-05) part of the official [snippets](https://github.com/atom/snippets) package !!!

># Available Snippets

>[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/frk1705/atom-available-snippets.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/frk1705/atom-available-snippets)

>Allows you to fuzzy search through all available snippets for your open document!

>![available-snippets-example](https://raw.github.com/frk1705/atom-available-snippets/master/docs/example.gif)

>## How to use

>You can activate the fuzzy selector by either:

>* The command palette: Search for `Available Snippets: Show`
>* Context-menu: Right click in your document and select `Show Available Snippets`
>* Key Shortcut: `alt-shift-s`

>## Contributions

>Contributors are welcome! Take a look at the [Atom contributing guide](https://github.com/atom/atom/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md).
